Denise Chiffon Berry and her son were driving in Hawthorne, California on Wednesday when a stranger in a Cadillac started shooting at them . 
  Ms Berry was pronounced dead at the scene while her 12-year-old son survived . 
  Police say the mother and son were simply laughing at the man in the car who had his legs dangling out of the window . 
  The man made eye contact with the boy and the mother told him 'Isn't that funny?' The man and two other men in the Cadillac were arrested and charged with murder . 
 